{
  "stem": "14724.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And by the time I was 15, I had every diploma, every certificate, every qualification you could name.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in the center of Swansea.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My foster father made trimmings for dress makers-- very well known everywhere.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what the Germans couldn't do to me in Germany, they tried to do to me in Swansea.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they bombed our house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the only thing I had was a little suitcase and a photograph of my parents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everything was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the main thing I need to tell was that when I was 10 and 1/2, I had a letter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'd only ever had one card from my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was in August, 1940-- no '39-- to tell me I had a sister, whose name was Zeilla.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I didn't hear anything after that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "January, February '42, I had a letter from the Red Cross to say that all my family had been sent to Riga-- my mother, four brothers, and two sisters.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as far as the Red Cross were concerned, they were dead.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They didn't say how they died, because they didn't know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Maybe-- maybe a week after I received that letter, the bomb came, smashed our house, and the house underneath, and it just about missed me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The letter was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And like every other normal child, I tried to erase this from my memory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was bad enough having to leave them, but to know they'd all died-- this I couldn't live with.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I couldn't acknowledge-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[DRINKS] For the moment I must return to my father, because he played another large part in my life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I had always believed-- because within two months, he arrived in England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After I arrived.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
